{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.16",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 16,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 16",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 16 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:2",
      "text": "I have often heard such things as these: you are all troublesome comforters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:3",
      "text": "Shall windy words have no end? or is it any trouble to thee to speak?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:4",
      "text": "I also could speak like you: and would God your soul were for my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:5",
      "text": "I would comfort you also with words, and would wag my head over you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:6",
      "text": "I would strengthen you with my mouth, and would move my lips, as sparing you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:7",
      "text": "But what shall I do? If I speak, my pain will not rest: and if I hold my peace, it will not depart from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:8",
      "text": "But now my sorrow hath oppressed me, and all my limbs are brought to nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:9",
      "text": "My wrinkles bear witness against me, and a false speaker riseth up against my face, contradicting me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:10",
      "text": "He hath gathered together his fury against me, and threatening me he hath gnashed with his teeth upon me: my enemy hath beheld me with terrible eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:11",
      "text": "They have opened their mouths upon me, and reproaching me they have struck me on the cheek, they are filled with my pains.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:12",
      "text": "God hath shut me up with the unjust man, and hath delivered me into the hands of the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:13",
      "text": "I that was formerly so wealthy, am all on a sudden broken to pieces: he hath taken me by my neck, he hath broken me, and hath set me up to be his mark.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:14",
      "text": "He hath compassed me round about with his lances, he hath wounded my loins, he hath not spared, and hath poured out my bowels on the earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:15",
      "text": "He hath torn me with wound upon wound, he hath rushed in upon me like a giant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:16",
      "text": "I have sowed sackcloth upon my skin, and have covered my flesh with ashes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:17",
      "text": "My face is swollen with weeping, and my eyelids are dim.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:18",
      "text": "These things have I suffered without the iniquity of my hand, when I offered pure prayers to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:19",
      "text": "O earth, cover not thou my blood, neither let my cry find a hiding place in thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:20",
      "text": "For behold my witness is in heaven, and he that knoweth my conscience is on high.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:21",
      "text": "My friends are full of words: my eye poureth out tears to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:22",
      "text": "And O that a man might so be judged with God, as the son of man is judged with his companion!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.16.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:23",
      "text": "For behold short years pass away, and I am walking in a path by which I shall not return.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
